Ephraim McDowell HIS Department Earns Ranking

BYLINE: The Harrodsburg Herald staff

LENGTH: 201  words


Ephraim McDowell Health's Information Services Department has earned a high
national ranking from a respected health care news organization.

In an effort to determine the best hospital IT workplaces in the United States,
Healthcare IT News sponsored a survey that looked at several critical IT areas.
Ephraim McDowell Health ranked ninth overall from 45 medium hospitals (101 to
350 licensed beds) across the nation that qualified for this honor. Overall,
Ephraim McDowell's Information Services Department was one of 272 hospitals
nominated for the Where to Work: Best Hospital IT Departments.

To earn this ranking, Ephraim McDowell's Information Services Department had to
be nominated for the Best Hospital IT Workplace, and then the Department's staff
completed an online survey. The survey measured employee satisfaction across a
number of key workplace categories, including leadership, management and
workplace conditions. Hospitals that earned ranking are those where employees
value a friendly, supportive workplace where they are empowered to do good work.

This award is further evidence that Ephraim McDowell Health's Information
Services Department upholds the organization's standard of excellence.

